Package: siscreenr
Title: Analyze Genome-Wide siRNA Screening Campaigns
Version: 2.5.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Aleksander",
           family = "Chlebowski",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "olobiolo@gmail.com")
Maintainer: <olobiolo@gmail.com>
Description: Data analysis tools for screening campaigns with a
    microscopic readout. Created to work with a genome-wide siRNA library
    and a ScanR imaging system, hence some idiosyncracies. Hopefully will
    be applicable to other setups as well.
License: GPL-3
URL: http://github.com/olobiolo/siscreenr
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: 
    magrittr (>= 1.5),
    dplyr (>= 0.7.8),
    tidyr (>= 0.8.2),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.1.0),
    data.table (>= 1.12.2),
    lubridate (>= 1.7.4),
    acutils (>= 0.1.0),
    reutils (>= 0.2.3),
    metamethods (>= 0.1.4)
Remotes: 
    olobiolo/metamethods
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
